ond to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705184,"age":5,"year":"1096","julianDay":2121366,"title":"The Crusades","description":"A series of religious wars between Christians and Muslims, known as the Crusades, occurred between 1096 and 1291, and played a large role in European Christian dominance in the Middle East.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/middle-ages/crusades","urlTitle":"History - The Crusades","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705185,"age":15,"year":"1106","julianDay":2125018,"title":"The Battle of Tichebray","description":"King Henry I defeated and captured his brother, Robert of Normandy, at the Battle of Tinchebray in 1106. Robert remained in captivity until his death in 1134.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When William FitzRaven was born in 1091, in Hatfield, Yorkshire, England, his father, Raven of Hatfield, was 30 and his mother, Mrs. Raven Hatfield, was 28. He married Mabel De Bosville. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. In 1148, his occupation is listed as sheriff of yorkshire . He died in 1164, at the age of 73."},"et":{"1091–1164":"1091–1164","1091–1121":"1091–1121","1120–1212":"1120–1212","1061–1100":"1061–1100","1063–Female":"1063–Surnud","1091":"1091","Aft 1100":"pärast 1100","1121":"1121","1164":"1164","1120":"1120","1096":"1096","1063":"1063","1061":"1061","1106":"1106","Between 1148 and 1159":"1148 kuni 1159","1212":"1212","1100":"1100","about 1120":"umbes 1120","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Hatfield, Yorkshire, England":"Hatfield, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1091–1164":"1091–1164","1091–1121":"1091–1121","1120–1212":"1120–1212","1061–1100":"1061–1100","1063–Female":"1063–Kuollut","1091":"1091","Aft 1100":"1100 jälkeen","1121":"1121","1164":"1164","1120":"1120","1096":"1096","1063":"1063","1061":"1061","1106":"1106","Between 1148 and 1159":"vuodesta 1148 vuoteen 1159","1212":"1212","1100":"1100","about 1